Price Index of Major Chinese Regions: Beijing 
Xinhua is releasing dispatches on major economic indicators of ten
major Chinese regions in the first three quarters of the year.
The ten regions include Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang, Henan,
Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing, Tianjin, and Chongqing. These provinces
and municipalities make up the bulk of the Chinese economy.
Following is the price situation in Beijing, the Chinese capital, in
the first three quarters of the year:
The consumer price index (CPI) in Beijing was 102.5 percent in the
first nine months, 0.8 percentage points higher than the first half of
this year. Retail price index (RPI) was 98.7 percent, only 0.1
percentage points more than the first half of this year.
